COLUMBIAN TITLE AND TRUST COMPANY, Trustee, v. SENECA FIRST STATE SAVINGS BANK OF SENECA, KANSAS, et al. No. 410. Circuit Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. March 9, 1931. Wheeler, Brewster & Hunt, of Topeka, Kan., for appellant. R. M. Emery, Jr., of Seneca, Kan., and J. Arthur Myers, of Topeka, Kan., for appellees.

Before LEWIS and PHILLIPS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed March 9,1931, per stipulation, at costs of appellant.
